ServisFirst Bancshares, Inc. Key Developments

ServisFirst Bancshares, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Reports Net Charge-Offs for the Second Quarter of 2017
Jul 17 17
ServisFirst Bancshares, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total interest income of USD 63,538,000 against USD 52,050,000 a year ago. Net interest income was USD 55,567,000 against USD 45,891,000 a year ago. Net interest income after provision for loan losses was USD 51,186,000 against USD 42,091,000 a year ago. Income before income tax was USD 34,116,000 against USD 26,434,000 a year ago. Net income was USD 24,164,000 against USD 18,876,000 a year ago. Net income available to common stockholders was USD 24,133,000 against USD 18,853,000 a year ago. Diluted earnings per common share were USD 0.45 against USD 0.36 a year ago. Book value per share was USD 10.72 as on June 30, 2017 against USD 9.32 as on June 30, 2016. Tangible book value per share – Non-GAAP was USD 10.44 as on June 30, 2017 against USD 9.03 as on June 30, 2016. Return on average assets was 1.55% against 1.37% a year ago. Return on average common stockholders' equity was 17.36% against 15.79% a year ago. Book value per share – GAAP was USD 10.72 as on June 30, 2017 against USD 9.32 as on June 30, 2016. 


For the six months, the company reported total interest income of USD 123,055,000 against USD 102,011,000 a year ago. Net interest income was USD 107,619,000 against USD 90,070,000 a year ago. Net interest income after provision for loan losses was USD 98,252,000 against USD 84,211,000 a year ago. Income before income tax was USD 64,461,000 against USD 52,699,000 a year ago. Net income was USD 46,683,000 against USD 38,832,000 a year ago. Net income available to common stockholders was USD 46,652,000 against USD 38,809,000 a year ago. Diluted earnings per common share were USD 0.86 against diluted earnings of USD 0.73 a year ago. Return on average assets was 1.55% against 1.37% a year ago. Return on average common stockholders' equity was 17.36% against 15.79% a year ago. 

For the quarter, the company reported net charge-offs of USD 3,214,000 against USD 1,947,000 a year ago.


ServisFirst Bancshares, Inc. to Report Q2, 2017 Results on Jul 17, 2017
Jun 30 17
ServisFirst Bancshares, Inc. announced that they will report Q2, 2017 results at 4:00 PM, US Eastern Standard Time on Jul 17, 2017


